nitf_LabelSubheader* nitf_LabelSubheader_construct ( nitf_Error *  error  ) 

Construct a new label subheader object. This object will be null set for every field. The object returned will be a full-fledged subheader, unless there is an error, in which case NULL will be returned, and the error object that was passed in will be populated.

Parameters:
error In case of error, when this function returns, this parameter will be populated
Returns:
The label subheader, or NULL on failure.

void nitf_LabelSubheader_destruct ( nitf_LabelSubheader **  subhdr  ) 

Destroy a label subheader object, and NULL-set the subheader. A double pointer is make the NULL-set persistant on function exit.

Parameters:
The address of the the label subheader pointer
